parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Seat Belt and Airbag System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt and airbag system can lead to the airbag warning indicator illuminating, and in the event of an accident, the airbags may not deploy properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: the airbag may not deploy in an accident

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Wiring Harness and Component Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of safety issues, including fires, stalling, and loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Sudden stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when occurring at intersections or while merging with traffic.
Intermittent electrical component failures can cause unpredictable behavior, leading to safety risks and driver frustration.
A fuel system failure can cause gasoline leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: gasoline spewing back out from the gas tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued fuel system failures, increasing the risk of accidents, fires, and explosions.
symptoms: Vehicle not included in recall despite similar symptoms
lack of proper diagnostic equipment and adapters.
